        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 9 at 4:42AM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 442 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles southwest of Hardesty, or 14 miles southeast of Guymon, moving
south at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Guymon, Perryton, Goodwell, Optima, Hardesty, Bryans Corner, Hough,
Adams, Farnsworth, Boyd, Waka, and Texhoma.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
